{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778904410105,"sessionID":"ses_1d10d6d4effeezfdc41LhV3iY2","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"functions.write:34","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/runner/work/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md","content":"Thank you @Clare72 for raising this. Changes committed in PR #<NN>.\n\nThe definition of **UBERON:0005162** *multi cell part structure* has been revised to allow for the presence of complete cells (e.g. glia in nervous-system regions), aligning with the FBbt change to `FBbt:00007060`. The new textual definition is:\n\n> \"A structure mainly consisting of cell components, rather than complete cells.\"\n\nA comment noting that such structures may contain complete cells in addition to partial ones has also been added. If any further adjustments are needed, please let us know.\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/runner/work/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"ISSUE_COMMENTS.md","time":{"start":1778904410100,"end":1778904410104}},"id":"prt_e2ef71cc3001iFaZral0kXXRW5","sessionID":"ses_1d10d6d4effeezfdc41LhV3iY2","messageID":"msg_e2ef70e1c001hAW1yWzijayLST"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778904424385,"sessionID":"ses_1d10d6d4effeezfdc41LhV3iY2","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"functions.write:35","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/runner/work/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/PR_COMMENTS.md","content":"## Summary\n\nThis PR revises the textual definition of **UBERON:0005162** *multi cell part structure* to resolve an inconsistency flagged in issue #3490 (and upstream in FBbt).\n\n### What changed\n\n| Field | Before | After |\n|-------|--------|-------|\n| `def` | \"A structure consisting of multiple cell components but which is not itself a cell and does not have (complete) cells as a part.\" | \"A structure mainly consisting of cell components, rather than complete cells.\" |\n| `comment` | *(none)* | \"May contain complete cells in addition to partial ones.\" |\n| `xref` | AAO:0011000, CARO:0001000, FMA:83115 | + **FBbt:00007060** |\n| `term_tracker_item` | *(none)* | https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/3490 |\n| `dc-contributor` | *(none)* | https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1373-1705 ! Clare Pilgrim |\n| `dcterms-date` | *(none)* | 2026-05-16T00:00:00Z |\n| `created_by` | *(none)* | dragon-ai-agent |\n\n### Rationale\n\nThe old definition explicitly excluded any complete cells as parts, which caused problems for many current subclasses—especially nervous-system regions such as neuropils and cell body rinds that routinely contain whole glial cells alongside partial neuronal projections. FlyBase already addressed the same problem in `FBbt:00007060` by broadening its definition; making the parallel change in Uberon keeps the two ontologies aligned and removes an implicit, biologically inaccurate exclusion.\n\nThe logical axiom `composed_primarily_of GO:0005575 ! cellular_component` already captures the intended meaning (\"mainly cell components\"), so no logical changes were required—only the textual definition needed updating.\n\n### Checklist\n\n- [x] Read issue text and linked FBbt issue carefully  \n- [x] Checked out target term (`obo-checkout.pl`) before editing  \n- [x] Verified logical axiom consistency with proposed definition  \n- [x] Added appropriate metadata (term tracker, contributor, date, agent)  \n- [x] Checked term back in (`obo-checkin.pl`)  \n- [x] Confirmed diff contains only intended changes in `src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo`  \n- [x] Committed with descriptive, signed message  \n\n### Signed-off\n\n@dragon-ai-agent\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/runner/work/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/PR_COMMENTS.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"PR_COMMENTS.md","time":{"start":1778904424377,"end":1778904424382}},"id":"prt_e2ef7284c001hHSw4f4Ka9oeWv","sessionID":"ses_1d10d6d4effeezfdc41LhV3iY2","messageID":"msg_e2ef70e1c001hAW1yWzijayLST"}}
