{"type":"text","timestamp":1778904440488,"sessionID":"ses_1d10d6d4effeezfdc41LhV3iY2","part":{"id":"prt_e2ef76b12001tEaUNybL1awIVR","messageID":"msg_e2ef7600e001B5npl8NX07szX0","sessionID":"ses_1d10d6d4effeezfdc41LhV3iY2","type":"text","text":"All done. Here's a summary of what I did:\n\n**Issue:** #3490 – FBbt revised `multi-cell component structure` to allow whole cells; asked UBERON to consider the same for `multi cell part structure` (UBERON:0005162).\n\n**Actions taken:**\n1. Checked out `UBERON:0005162` into `terms/`.\n2. Revised its textual definition from  \n   *\"A structure consisting of multiple cell components but which is not itself a cell and does not have (complete) cells as a part.\"*  \n   to  \n   *\"A structure mainly consisting of cell components, rather than complete cells.\"*\n3. Added a comment: *\"May contain complete cells in addition to partial ones.\"*\n4. Added `xref: FBbt:00007060` to formalise the cross-ontology linkage.\n5. Added metadata: `term_tracker_item`, `dc-contributor` (Clare Pilgrim, found ORCID 0000-0002-1373-1705), `dcterms-date`, and `created_by: dragon-ai-agent`.\n6. Checked the term back in and committed the resulting diff in `src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo`.\n\n**Result:** The definition is now consistent with the recent FBbt revision and correctly reflects that many subclasses (nervous-system regions with glia, etc.) contain whole cells, while remaining aligned with the existing logical axiom `composed_primarily_of GO:0005575 ! cellular_component`.\n\n**Files left for you to feed back:**\n- `ISSUE_COMMENTS.md`\n- `PR_COMMENTS.md`\n\nLet me know if you need anything else!","time":{"start":1778904427282,"end":1778904440486}}}
